  "commentary": "With SPX at 6604.8 sitting just below the flip at 6610 in a PIN regime, dealers are currently long gamma and will sell any rally toward the massive 28.6B wall at 6605, creating immediate resistance. The recent wall break and GEX surge events suggest we just punched through a key level, but the heavy positive gamma concentration from 6605-6620 should act as a magnet, pulling price back toward this zone with dealers providing stabilizing flows. Watch 6590 closely as the major negative gamma strike - any break below triggers amplified selling as dealers flip to short gamma hedging.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pulled back toward 6605-6610 with limited upside past 6620.",
